        <abstract>
            <p>Criticises Duke of Argyll’s address [to the Royal Society of Edinburgh (1864)] and demurs on Argyll’s "new birth" theory.</p>
            <p>Agrees with CL on beauty.</p>
            <p>Enjoyed hearing of Princess Royal’s discussion [on Darwinism].</p>
            <p>CD’s illness.</p> 
<p>CL’s advice on chapter [of <hi rend="italic">Variation</hi>] on dogs was excellent.</p> 
        </abstract>
